	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can get from level 16-20 hunting in Lake Rathe. It is probably a lot less crowded these days becuase of the expansions. In lake rathe there are level 16-20 aviak guards that you can fight. They are an undercon for their level, and you will be able to take the level 20 ones at level 16. You can get to level 23/24 on the guards.<br><br>At level 20 you can also go to south karana and fight aviaks in the aviak village with other people. Or you can fight the hermit in south karana. The hermit is located in a house in a stone ring in the middle of nowhere in south karana. If you ask someone they will probably be able to tell you the loc. He is level 20, and to get him to come out of his house, you say "kill you". If you say that right next to the chimney of the house he will come and start attacking you, and at that time you will be able to kill him. He respawns every 3 minutes, so you will have just enough time to med before you kill him again. After you have killed him once all you have to do is target your pet and then type /target, and it will automatically target the hermit, through the wall once he has spawned. You can get to level 28 on the hermit.<br><br>In the low 20's there are also some other things to fight in south K. There are the gnolls that spawn outside of blackburrow around the big claws, and there are the treants that drop a lot of money. <br><br>In east karana there is a druid ring where 3 druids and treants spawn every 3 MINUTES. They drop AMAZINGLY good loot and are AWESOME exp. a group of 4-5 casters in the low 20's to high 20's can take them. The druids will give you absolutely NO faction hit but the treants in east karana and south karana will lower your faction with qeynos and a couple other things I can't remeber. It is well worth it though if you decide to fight them.<br><br>See the guide i wrote on this forum for more informtion on place to hunt, becuase I don't want to re-tpye it all.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
