	   <tr><td colspan=2>Everyone is going to tell you to go to Oasis cause the crocs down there are great xp.&nbsp;&nbsp;What they dont tell you is that there always 40 others there hunting those same crocs, making that "great" xp, pretty $hitty.  <br><br>There are two good spots for xp, but you gotta have some serious nutz to hunt at them.<br><br>1) Unrest - Hunt beetles.  The higher level players in the zone will thank you for clearing out this yard trash and there is always tons of them after that you can move on to tormented dead and jack-o-lanterns(love kill'n those things).  BUT, be VERY careful when doing so.  Unrest should be called the "Amtrak zone" for the constant trains that come through.  Generally speaking, if a train comes through, you can just press up against the wall just outside the enterance tunnel and you'll be *just* outside of the train's aggro range.  I soloed very successfully there until 20 (then you need to go inside the house to get xp which I DONT recomend.<br><br>2) Lake of Ill Omen - This Kunark zone is about the best hunting I have done since Crushbone.  Great xp, plenty of critters, almost no trains and you can hunt there til you are in your mid to late 20's.  But here is the catch.  To get there you have to go to Firivona Vie (for good races).  Between FV and Omen is a rather large field of really nasty critters called Drachnids.  I have had the unfortunate opportunity to discover some of these 30+ mobs can see invisible.  Others have also told me they can root and sow themselves as well.  Worst part is that they are swarming everywhere.  <br>Once you get past them and zone into Omen, you are relatively safe.  <br>One more Omen safety tip.  Stay out of the water.  The lake is inhabited by 40ish goblins and the pond has sturgeon that will chew up and spit out a 16th leveler in no time. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
